The Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) have joined other well meaning Nigerians and chieftains of the All Progressive Congress (APC) in felicitating with Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, the National Chairman of the party on his 68th birthday. Governor of Kebbi State, Alhaji Abubakar Atiku Bagudu, who is the chairman of the Forum on Saturday signed a congratulatory message to greet the National Chairman. The message read in part “we celebrate this special occasion with Your Excellency and your entire family. “We in particular wish to acknowledge and commend your commitment to a united prosperous Nigeria. “We also acknowledge your contributions as one of the founding members of this Forum and continues inputs to the processes of managing governance  in Nigeria. “As our National Chairman, we join your family, our party members and all Nigerians to celebrate you. “Congratulations and Happy Birthday to Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. We rejoice with you and wish you a happy birthday”. The Progressive Governors Forum also  called  on  Nigerians to observe all measures put in place to curtail the spreading of current Covid -19 such as social distancing  and stay safe as the Federal Government w strive  towards overcoming the  global pandemic. The APC governors commended all front-line medical personnel under the leadership of the Federal Ministry of Health and National Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) and pray that God continue to guide the country and the world to succeed to bring to an immediate end this world pandemic.